core_data_meta.Z_PK: Primary key per table row (managed by Core Data style allocator via Z_PRIMARYKEY.Z_MAX).
core_data_meta.Z_ENT: Core Data entity id. Use rich model expected entity id per table.
core_data_meta.Z_OPT: Core Data optimistic locking/version field; commonly starts at 1 and increments on update.

timestamps.storage_format: Apple Cocoa reference date seconds since 2001-01-01T00:00:00Z (REAL/NUMERIC values in SQLite).
write_guidance: Convert app DateTime to Cocoa seconds (UTC).
For jump date-only UX, preserve existing convention (historically often midday local converted to UTC) to avoid date shifting across time zones.

write_contract.goal: Continue using the same SQLite DB with a new app while preserving historical rich-model entries.

rich_model_only_policy.description: When reading/writing app data, use rows whose Z_ENT matches the canonical entity id in Z_PRIMARYKEY for each table.

insert_rules: Always wrap inserts/updates affecting Z_PK rows in a transaction.
Allocate Z_PK through Z_PRIMARYKEY.Z_MAX for the target entity before insert.
Set Z_ENT to canonical entity id; set Z_OPT to 1 on insert (increment on update).
Store timestamps in Cocoa epoch seconds.
Use LEFT JOIN in reads for optional/orphan relationships (especially rig links).
Do not assume every rich jump has photos/signature/brake setting.
update_rules: Update ZLOGENTRY row by Z_PK and canonical Z_ENT filter.
Increment Z_OPT when modifying a row (Core Data optimistic lock style).
Replace rig links in Z_5RIGS transactionally if UI edits rig selection.
delete_rules_recommended: Soft-delete is not modeled for ZLOGENTRY in schema. If implementing hard delete, also cleanup ZLOGENTRYIMAGE and Z_5RIGS rows in app transaction.
Do NOT rely on SQLite cascade (no FK constraints/triggers in DB).

sql_queries_ready.list_rich_jumps_summary:
SELECT
  le.Z_PK,
  le.ZJUMPNUMBER,
  le.ZDATE,
  le.ZNOTES,
  obj.ZNAME AS ObjectName,
  obj.ZOBJECTTYPE AS ObjectType,
  obj.ZREGION AS ObjectRegion,
  jt.ZNAME AS JumpType,
  dt.ZNAME AS DeploymentType,
  pc.ZNAME AS PilotChuteType,
  st.ZNAME AS SliderType,
  r.ZNAME AS RigName,
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ZLOGENTRYIMAGE li
     WHERE li.Z_ENT = 6
       AND li.ZLOGENTRY = le.Z_PK) AS ImageCount
FROM ZLOGENTRY le
LEFT JOIN ZOBJECT obj
       ON obj.Z_PK = le.ZOBJECT
      AND obj.Z_ENT = 7
LEFT JOIN ZJUMPTYPE jt
       ON jt.Z_PK = le.ZJUMPTYPE
      AND jt.Z_ENT = 3
LEFT JOIN ZDEPLOYMENTTYPE dt
       ON dt.Z_PK = le.ZDEPLOYMENTTYPE
      AND dt.Z_ENT = 2
LEFT JOIN ZPILOTCHUTETYPE pc
       ON pc.Z_PK = le.ZPILOTCHUTETYPE
      AND pc.Z_ENT = 9
LEFT JOIN ZSLIDERTYPE st
       ON st.Z_PK = le.ZSLIDERTYPE
      AND st.Z_ENT = 13
LEFT JOIN Z_5RIGS j5
       ON j5.Z_5LOGENTRIES = le.Z_PK
LEFT JOIN ZRIG r
       ON r.Z_PK = j5.Z_10RIGS
      AND r.Z_ENT = 10
WHERE le.Z_ENT = 5
ORDER BY le.ZJUMPNUMBER DESC;
sql_queries_ready.get_rich_jump_detail_by_pk:
SELECT
  le.*,
  obj.ZNAME AS ObjectName,
  obj.ZOBJECTTYPE AS ObjectType,
  obj.ZREGION AS ObjectRegion,
  obj.ZLATITUDE,
  obj.ZLONGITUDE,
  obj.ZHEIGHT,
  obj.ZHEIGHTUNIT,
  jt.ZNAME AS JumpType,
  dt.ZNAME AS DeploymentType,
  pc.ZNAME AS PilotChuteType,
  st.ZNAME AS SliderType,
  bs.ZNAME AS BrakeSetting
FROM ZLOGENTRY le
LEFT JOIN ZOBJECT obj ON obj.Z_PK = le.ZOBJECT AND obj.Z_ENT = 7
LEFT JOIN ZJUMPTYPE jt ON jt.Z_PK = le.ZJUMPTYPE AND jt.Z_ENT = 3
LEFT JOIN ZDEPLOYMENTTYPE dt ON dt.Z_PK = le.ZDEPLOYMENTTYPE AND dt.Z_ENT = 2
LEFT JOIN ZPILOTCHUTETYPE pc ON pc.Z_PK = le.ZPILOTCHUTETYPE AND pc.Z_ENT = 9
LEFT JOIN ZSLIDERTYPE st ON st.Z_PK = le.ZSLIDERTYPE AND st.Z_ENT = 13
LEFT JOIN ZBRAKESETTING bs ON bs.Z_PK = le.ZBRAKESETTING AND bs.Z_ENT = 1
WHERE le.Z_ENT = 5
  AND le.Z_PK = :jumpPk;
sql_queries_ready.get_rich_jump_rigs_by_jump_pk:
SELECT
  j5.Z_5LOGENTRIES AS JumpPk,
  j5.Z_10RIGS AS RigPk,
  r.ZNAME,
  r.ZISARCHIVED,
  r.ZUNIQUEID
FROM Z_5RIGS j5
LEFT JOIN ZRIG r
       ON r.Z_PK = j5.Z_10RIGS
      AND r.Z_ENT = 10
WHERE j5.Z_5LOGENTRIES = :jumpPk
ORDER BY r.ZNAME COLLATE NOCASE, RigPk;
sql_queries_ready.get_rich_jump_images_meta_by_jump_pk:
SELECT
  li.Z_PK,
  li.ZLOGENTRY,
  li.ZMD5,
  length(li.ZIMAGE) AS ImageBytes
FROM ZLOGENTRYIMAGE li
WHERE li.Z_ENT = 6
  AND li.ZLOGENTRY = :jumpPk
ORDER BY li.Z_PK;
sql_queries_ready.insert_rich_jump_template:
-- Execute inside the same transaction used for Z_PRIMARYKEY allocation for entity 5
INSERT INTO ZLOGENTRY (
    Z_PK, Z_ENT, Z_OPT,
    ZDELAY, ZEXITWINDSPEED, ZGROUNDWINDSPEED, ZJUMPNUMBER, ZOPENINGDIRECTION,
    ZBRAKESETTING, ZDEPLOYMENTTYPE, ZJUMPTYPE, ZOBJECT, ZPILOTCHUTETYPE, ZSIGNATURE, ZSLIDERTYPE,
    ZDATE, ZLASTMODIFIEDUTC, ZLASTSIGNATUREUTC,
    ZEXITWINDDIRECTION, ZEXITWINDSPEEDUNIT, ZGROUNDWINDDIRECTION, ZGROUNDWINDSPEEDUNIT,
    ZNOTES, ZUNIQUEID
) VALUES (
    :Z_PK, 5, :Z_OPT,
    :ZDELAY, :ZEXITWINDSPEED, :ZGROUNDWINDSPEED, :ZJUMPNUMBER, :ZOPENINGDIRECTION,
    :ZBRAKESETTING, :ZDEPLOYMENTTYPE, :ZJUMPTYPE, :ZOBJECT, :ZPILOTCHUTETYPE, :ZSIGNATURE, :ZSLIDERTYPE,
    :ZDATE, :ZLASTMODIFIEDUTC, :ZLASTSIGNATUREUTC,
    :ZEXITWINDDIRECTION, :ZEXITWINDSPEEDUNIT, :ZGROUNDWINDDIRECTION, :ZGROUNDWINDSPEEDUNIT,
    :ZNOTES, :ZUNIQUEID
);
